snippet: At least six people died and 14 others were injured when a building that was being demolished collapsed on a Salvation Army store.
abstract: Rescuers in Philadelphia end their search for survivors and victims of a city-center building collapse on Salvation Army store that left six people dead and 13 injured; focus turns to whether demolition contractor Griffin Campbell Construction had necessary expertise to safely demolish building next to one still being used.

byline.contributor: Dan Barry, Jack Begg and Timothy Williams contributed reporting from New York.

lead_paragraph: At least six people died and 14 others were injured when a building that was being demolished collapsed on a Salvation Army store.

headline.main: Focus in Philadelphia Building Collapse Turns to Demolition Contractor’s Expertise
headline.print_headline: Focus in Philadelphia Building Collapse Turns to Demolition Contractor’s Expertise
